Premiere Voice AI User Guide
Overview

Premiere Voice AI is an Adobe Premiere Pro extension that allows you to generate, import, and modify AI-powered voiceovers directly within your editing workflow.

The plugin enables users to create narration, voiceovers, explainer audio, and dialogue tracks without leaving Premiere Pro.

Features
AI voice generation from text
Multiple voice and gender options
Tone selection for different speaking styles
Speed and pitch controls
Custom file naming
Import generated audio directly into the timeline
Import generated audio into the project bin
Modify existing AI-generated clips
Load previous generation settings from selected clips
Persistent metadata for easy editing and regeneration
Getting Started
1. Open the Plugin

Launch Adobe Premiere Pro and open the Premiere Voice AI panel from the Extensions menu.

2. Configure Voice Settings

Select:

Gender
Voice
Tone
Filename (optional)
Speed
Pitch
3. Enter Your Script

Type or paste the text you want to convert into speech.

4. Generate Audio

Click Generate Voice.

The plugin will generate a voiceover using the selected settings.

Importing Audio
Import to Timeline

Click Import to Timeline to place the generated audio directly into the active sequence at the current playhead position.

Import to Bin

Click Import to Bin to add the generated audio to your Premiere Pro project without placing it on the timeline.

Editing Existing Voice Clips
Load Selected Clip

Select a previously generated Premiere Voice AI clip in the timeline.

Click Load Selected Clip.

The plugin will automatically load:

Original text
Voice selection
Gender
Tone
Speed
Pitch
Filename

This allows you to continue editing without recreating settings manually.

Modify Selected Clip

After loading a clip:

Change the text and/or voice settings
Click Modify Selected Clip

The selected clip will be updated using the new settings while maintaining its position in the timeline.

Voice Controls
Tone

Choose a speaking style that best matches your content:

Professional
Documentary
Voiceover
Dynamic
Casual
Comedic
Serious
Custom
Speed

Adjust the speaking rate of the generated voice.

Lower values create slower narration.

Higher values create faster delivery.

Pitch

Adjust the vocal pitch of the generated voice.

Negative values lower the voice.

Positive values raise the voice.

Metadata System

Every generated voice file includes metadata that stores:

Original text
Voice selection
Gender
Tone
Speed
Pitch
Filename
Creation details

This metadata allows the plugin to restore generation settings when editing existing clips.

Best Practices
Use concise punctuation for natural speech.
Break long scripts into paragraphs.
Preview generated voiceovers before final delivery.
Use descriptive filenames for easier project management.
Keep generated audio files and metadata files together.
Troubleshooting
No Voice Generated

Verify that:

The backend service is running.
A valid voice is selected.
Text has been entered.
Premiere Pro has an active project open.
Cannot Modify Clip

Ensure that:

The selected clip was originally generated by Premiere Voice AI.
The clip is still linked to its generated media file.
The associated metadata file is available.
Voice Settings Not Loading

Ensure that:

The selected clip is a Premiere Voice AI-generated clip.
Metadata files have not been moved or deleted.
Workflow Example
Enter script text
Select voice settings
Generate Voice
Import to Timeline
Review in sequence
Select clip later
Load Selected Clip
Make changes
Modify Selected Clip

This workflow allows rapid iteration without manually recreating voice settings each time.
